nd that the dispersion decreases when examining the\nhighest redshifts, where only pointed observations are available. These results\nfurther confirm that quasars are `standardisable candles', that is we can\nreliably measure cosmological distances at high redshifts where very few\ncosmological probes are available.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Sep 2021 18:00:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-01"}
